                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="soul"></a>Soul Symphony Choir, Tuesday evenings at 7.15</h3>
                <p>Soul Symphony Choir is a fun, friendly and vibrant choir based in Croydon, and is directed by the amazingly talented Joanne Miller. Soul Symphony Choir is more than entertainment; its members enjoy helping our community and reaching out to those who may appear to be less integrated into society. Soul Symphony has raised thousands of pounds through fundraising concerts for charities and causes. You are welcome to join us on Tuesday evenings from 7:15pm at Emmanuel Centre, Rockhampton Road, South Croydon CR2 7AQ, opposite St Peter’s Primary School and Emmanuel Church. For more information please visit <%= link_to "www.soulsymphony.co.uk", "http://www.soulsymphony.co.uk" %>.</p>
